		<h2 id="title">About Timenite</h1>
    <div id="blog">

	<p>Timenite is a simple website made for the Fortnite Community that tracks the endings <br>
	                   of every ongoing season, Item Shop reset time and the upcoming events.<br></p>
	                   
                   	<p>My name is <a href="https://priyamraj.com">Priyam Raj</a> and the idea to make this website came to me in 2018 when Season 4 was about to end and <br>
                    since I really loved the game, I kept it open all the time on the last day of Season <br>
                    just to see the Countdown Timer in the BattlePass Page. <br> </p>
                    
                 
                    
                   	<p> And because of this, I cannot use my PC as Fortnite takes a lot of RAM Usage <br>
                    even when running in the Background and I know, there are YouTube Channels that Stream <br> 
                    the same kind of Countdowns but I don't like it either because constantly running a video <br> 
                    is not a Good idea either so I made Timenite, a simple solution for all that. </p>
                    <br>
                    
                    
                      <p>You can read more about Timenite, <a href="https://priyamraj.com/project/countdown-for-fortnites-upcoming-seasons/">here</a>.</p> 
                      <br>
                    
	<p><strong>Why use Timenite?</strong> <br>
                    Well, there are many reasons why you should Bookmark Timenite.com <br>
                    right now if you're a Fortnite Player. <br> </p>
                    
                      	<p><strong>It Loads Fast:</strong> It loads up really fast even if you have a slow internet connection.<br> Also, once it loads, Timenite can still work even if you turn off your Internet. </p>
                      	
                        <p><strong>It's Lightweight:</strong> It barely uses your data (in Kilobytes)  so don't worry <br>about it being exhausted. </p>
                        
</div>

                    

	



